-- Kazakhstan's Halyk Bank first-half net profit soars 87 pct
-- By Mariya Gordeyeva
-- Fri Aug 22, 2014 01:52AM EDT
-- None



ALMATY, Aug 22 (Reuters) - Halyk Bank <HSBK.KZ>, Kazakhstan's second-largest lender by assets, said on Friday its first-half net profit soared 87.4 percent to 64 billion tenge ($352 million) from a year earlier.    ($1 = 182 tenge)   (Reporting by Mariya Gordeyeva; Writing by Dmitry Solovyov; Editing by Anand Basu)  ((dmitry.solovyov@thomsonreuters.com; +7 727 3300 787 x 705; Reuters Messaging: dmitry.solovyov.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: HALYK BANK RESULTS/

